      "amount": "3-4 tablespoons",
      "notes": "Guaranteed organic, low sodium"
    },
    {
      "name": "Garlic Paste",
      "amount": "2 cloves (finely chopped)",
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "Ginger Paste",
      "amount": "1 inch piece (finely minced)",
      "notes": ""
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Place prawns in a pot and add a pinch of salt.",
    "Cover and heat over medium-high heat until the prawns turn pink, about 5 minutes.",
    "Remove from heat and drain prawns into a mixing bowl.",
    "In the same pan, add almonds and pistachios to the remaining oil and cook for about 30 seconds until fragrant.",
    "Add garlic paste and ginger paste to the pan. Cook for an additional minute while stirring constantly.",
    "Pour in soy sauce and stir continuously for another 1-2 minutes until mixture thickens slightly.",
    "Combine prawns with nutty-ginger-sauce and toss gently."
